.TH GIT\-ISSUE\-CREATE 1 "2026-02-07" "git-issue 0.5.0" "Git Issue Manual"
.SH NAME
git\-issue\-create \- create a new issue
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git issue create
.RI [ options ]
.I <title>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Create a new issue in the current repository.
A UUID is generated for the issue and stored as a ref under
.BR refs/issues/ .
The root commit contains the title, optional body, and metadata
as Git trailers.
.PP
On success, the 7-character abbreviated issue ID is printed.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-message " " \fI<text>\fR
Issue description (body text).
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-label " " \fI<label>\fR
Add a label.
Can be repeated to add multiple labels.
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-assignee " " \fI<email>\fR
Assign the issue to someone.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-priority " " \fI<level>\fR
Set priority.
Must be one of:
.BR low ", " medium ", " high ", " critical .
.TP
.BI \-\-milestone " " <name>
Set the milestone.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Create a simple issue:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue create "Fix login timeout"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Create an issue with metadata:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue create "Fix login timeout" \\
    -m "Users report 30s hangs on slow networks" \\
    -l bug -l urgent -p high -a dev@example.com
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git\-issue (1),
.BR git\-issue\-show (1),
.BR git\-issue\-edit (1)
